# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# .env.v2.example — govOS v2 authentication and service configuration
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# Copy this to .env.v2 in the repo root and fill in your actual credentials.
# .env.v2 is gitignored; never commit real secrets.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OAuth Providers — GitHub
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Register at: https://github.com/settings/developers
# Set Authorization callback URL to: https://auth.12sgi.com/api/v2/auth/github/callback
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OAuth Providers — Google
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Register at: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# Create OAuth 2.0 Client ID (Web application)
# Add Authorized redirect URI: https://auth.12sgi.com/api/v2/auth/google/callback
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OAuth Providers — Apple Sign-In
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Register at: https://developer.apple.com/account/resources/identifiers/list
# Configure "Sign in with Apple"
# Set Return URL to: https://auth.12sgi.com/api/v2/auth/apple/callback
APPLE_CLIENT_ID=
APPLE_TEAM_ID=
APPLE_KEY_ID=
APPLE_PRIVATE_KEY=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OAuth Providers — Microsoft / Azure Entra
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Register at: https://portal.azure.com → Azure Active Directory → App registrations
# Set Redirect URI to: https://auth.12sgi.com/api/v2/auth/microsoft/callback
MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID=
MICROSOFT_CLIENT_SECRET=
MICROSOFT_TENANT_ID=common

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Magic Links via Email
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SMTP configuration for sending magic link emails.
# Tested with: Gmail (SMTP), SendGrid, Mailgun, AWS SES.
# Gmail requires an app password; never put the normal Google account password here.
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=
SMTP_PASS=
SMTP_FROM=noreply@12sgi.com
SMTP_STARTTLS=true
SMTP_ALLOW_UNAUTHENTICATED=false
MAGIC_LINK_TTL_SECONDS=900
MAGIC_LINK_MIN_INTERVAL_SECONDS=60

# Local inference default sized for an 8 GB laptop GPU.
GPU_DEFAULT_MODEL=llama3.2

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Auth Service Configuration
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Strong random secret for signing JWTs. Generate with:
#   python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"
AUTH_SIGNING_SECRET=

# Internal service-to-service token (used by services calling /api/v2/auth/introspect).
# Generate with:
#   python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"
INTERNAL_SERVICE_TOKEN=

# Public URL of the auth service (used in OAuth callbacks, emails, etc.).
AUTH_PUBLIC_URL=https://auth.12sgi.com

# Where the console redirects to after successful sign-in (token appended as #token=...).
OAUTH_REDIRECT_BASE=https://12sgi.com/king/

# CORS-allowed origins for the console frontend.
CORS_ORIGINS=https://jimlangford.github.io,https://12sgi.com

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Owner Access Control
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Comma-separated allowlists of GitHub logins and email addresses that can sign in.
# Matching is case-insensitive.
OWNER_GITHUB_LOGINS=jimlangford
OWNER_GOOGLE_EMAILS=jimlangford@me.com,elementlotus@gmail.com,jimmylangford@elementlotus.com,JRCSL@12sgi.com
OWNER_APPLE_EMAILS=jimlangford@me.com,elementlotus@gmail.com,jimmylangford@elementlotus.com,JRCSL@12sgi.com
OWNER_MAGIC_EMAILS=jimlangford@me.com,elementlotus@gmail.com,jimmylangford@elementlotus.com,jrcsl@12sgi.com
OWNER_PASSKEY_EMAILS=jimlangford@me.com,elementlotus@gmail.com,jimmylangford@elementlotus.com,jrcsl@12sgi.com

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WebAuthn / Passkeys Configuration
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Domain for passkey registration and verification.
WEBAUTHN_RP_ID=12sgi.com
# Full origin (scheme + domain + port if non-standard).
WEBAUTHN_ORIGIN=https://12sgi.com

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Development Flags
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Allow the published dev secrets (fail-closed unless this is set to 1).
# Only set to 1 for local/Tailscale-private dev. NEVER in production.
GOVOS_ALLOW_DEV_SECRETS=0

# Enable diagnostic endpoints (e.g., /api/v2/auth/diagnostics/claims).
# Only enable for debugging; should be 0 in production.
AUTH_VERIFICATION_DIAGNOSTICS_ENABLED=0
